  "example_section_data": {
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "The generalized Laguerre polynomials are closely related to the confluent\nhypergeometric function :math:`{}_1F_1`:"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "    .. math::\n        L_n^{(\\alpha)} = \\binom{n + \\alpha}{n} {}_1F_1(-n, \\alpha +1, x)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "This can be verified, for example,  for :math:`n = \\alpha = 3` over the\ninterval :math:`[-1, 1]`:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "import numpy as np\nfrom scipy.special import binom\nfrom scipy.special import genlaguerre\nfrom scipy.special import hyp1f1\nx = np.arange(-1.0, 1.0, 0.01)\nnp.allclose(genlaguerre(3, 3)(x), binom(6, 3) * hyp1f1(-3, 4, x))"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "This is the plot of the generalized Laguerre polynomials\n:math:`L_3^{(\\alpha)}` for some values of :math:`\\alpha`:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nx = np.arange(-4.0, 12.0, 0.01)\nfig, ax = plt.subplots()\nax.set_ylim(-5.0, 10.0)\nax.set_title(r'Generalized Laguerre polynomials $L_3^{\\alpha}$')\nfor alpha in np.arange(0, 5):\n    ax.plot(x, genlaguerre(3, alpha)(x), label=rf'$L_3^{(alpha)}$')\nplt.legend(loc='best')\nplt.show()"
      },
